00:22:09,360 --> 00:22:10,060
No.

318
00:22:11,140 --> 00:22:12,400
Do we really need a plaster cast?

319
00:22:13,440 --> 00:22:14,680
Generally,

320
00:22:14,990 --> 00:22:17,160
before we have students do portrait sketches,

321
00:22:17,190 --> 00:22:18,920
we have them practice with plaster casts

322
00:22:18,940 --> 00:22:21,980
to test and train their sketching abilities.

323
00:22:24,720 --> 00:22:25,910
But since I

324
00:22:26,200 --> 00:22:28,200
rarely draw portraits myself,

325
00:22:28,870 --> 00:22:30,470
I don't have an example for you to reference.

326
00:22:32,700 --> 00:22:35,080
Or can I draw you?

327
00:22:37,110 --> 00:22:37,950
Me?

328
00:22:38,640 --> 00:22:39,390
Yes.

329
00:22:39,690 --> 00:22:41,020
You've already told me about

330
00:22:41,040 --> 00:22:43,270
the three sides and five values of sketching last time.

331
00:22:43,520 --> 00:22:44,850
I'll give it a try first.

332
00:22:44,880 --> 00:22:46,320
You can tell me how to adjust later.

333
00:22:50,300 --> 00:22:54,400
Alright, but let me explain something first.

334
00:22:54,870 --> 00:22:56,070
Last time I mentioned that

335
00:22:56,070 --> 00:23:00,330
there are some small details in your sketching

336
00:23:00,570 --> 00:23:01,750
that you could pay more attention to.

337
00:23:02,640 --> 00:23:04,050
It's not about technique.

338
00:23:05,610 --> 00:23:07,550
What I told you last time was about observation.

339
00:23:08,220 --> 00:23:11,020
You need to observe more carefully.

340
00:23:12,120 --> 00:23:14,310
Come on, stand up.

341
00:23:14,800 --> 00:23:15,560
Stand up?

342
00:23:15,810 --> 00:23:16,440
Yes.

343
00:23:20,540 --> 00:23:23,090
Stand back. Stand away from me.

344
00:23:25,170 --> 00:23:25,900
Back.

345
00:23:28,500 --> 00:23:29,380
Okay, stop.

346
00:23:31,210 --> 00:23:32,500
Now, look into my eyes

347
00:23:33,810 --> 00:23:34,840
and observe me carefully.

348
00:23:37,380 --> 00:23:38,400
Is the me you see now

349
00:23:39,280 --> 00:23:40,540
a little different from

350
00:23:41,770 --> 00:23:42,990
the me you usually see?

351
00:23:44,990 --> 00:23:46,030
It seems so.

352
00:23:47,920 --> 00:23:48,670
Okay.

353
00:23:49,520 --> 00:23:53,630
Now, slowly walk towards me.

354
00:23:55,130 --> 00:23:55,950
Slowly.

355
00:23:57,720 --> 00:23:58,490
Move forward.

356
00:24:01,650 --> 00:24:02,560
Don't look away.

357
00:24:03,030 --> 00:24:03,950
Look into my eyes.

358
00:24:04,930 --> 00:24:06,160
Keep your eyes on mine.

359
00:24:08,810 --> 00:24:09,920
Come on, move forward.

360
00:24:14,010 --> 00:24:14,570
Forward.

361
00:24:18,290 --> 00:24:19,080
Move forward.

362
00:24:32,280 --> 00:24:33,000
Now,

363
